message: It doesn’t hurt to just put the lyrics in the native language, Karakalpak, along with its IPA pronunciation on this article. The other transcriptions can stay away, as they are unnecessary and can be a burden on some users.

Those are not translations, but are the various writing systems that have been historically used in the past to write Gagauz, and it does not hurt to put them here. Other writing systems does NOT mean other translations. Discuss on talk page.
The [[Common Turkic Alphabet]] for Turkmen is not the [[Turkish language]] exactly, but a rendering of the Niyazov/Turkmenbashi Latin alphabet into Common Turkic ones.
